{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3066163-0d82-4b8c-8d07-b186d3f03935","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` — it monitors file changes and re-runs tests automatically:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag focuses on just your failing test. When you save changes to `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, it re-builds and re-runs automatically.\n\n**Quick tip on the bug:** `RemoveStock` never validates — it just subtracts. You'll need to add a guard like:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to start the watch session and apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b521c65-96b0-4186-8b16-313e4ef94b63","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for their test project. With .NET and the Microsoft Testing Platform (as configured in global.json), they can use `dotnet watch test` or `dotnet test --hot-reload`. Let me check what's available.\n\nActually, with `dotnet watch`, you can run `dotnet watch test` which will re-run tests whenever files change. That's the standard hot-reload approach for test projects.\n\nLet me also note the bug - `RemoveStock` doesn't throw when the quantity exceeds available stock; it just goes negative. But the user asked about hot reload setup, not about fixing the bug itself.\n\n\nI'll walk them through setting up `dotnet watch test` so their tests automatically re-run as they make changes.","outputTokens":382,"requestId":"5C26:13E575:28AE84:32472C:69F5546D"},"id":"58289cf7-3a48-43c8-8c57-6eb6720e37ee","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:33:50.401Z","parentId":"b86bb2a3-4b92-4ca4-a8c1-6251dd7c45c7"}
